Maxine Waters, or Auntie Maxine as we lovingly call her, has been been a fearless leader of justice for years.
As we all know, Waters is enemy number one for Trump, but that hasn’t stopped her activism or fighting spirit.
Now, she has made history as the first woman and African American to be the chair of the House Financial Services Committee.
